A biography of the late Gore Vidal, looking at the life of one of America's leading literary figures who for years entranced and enraged the US with his outspoken views, novels and essays. First aired in two parts on the BBC, 9 and 16 October 1995 and again on 12 and 19 August 2012.  Part 1 follows Vidal around the scenes of his youth; in Part 2  Vidal recalls the last 35 years of his life, starting from the time his friend John F Kennedy was elected as US president.  
